caption: Delicious food
Best Thai in the neighborhood
Had a great experience in this spot with my daughter. The food came quick and the customer service is just awesome. Prices are fair.

I always ordered from this place when I worked in the neighborhood. I was back in the city today and decided to get drunken noodles. I didn’t look at the food until I got back home. It was a total disaster. The food looked unappetizing and tasted like a meal for geriatrics. The noodles were all broken up into tiny pieces and looked like smashed ziti noodles. Extremely soft and mushy and chipped into tiny pieces. I am terribly disappointed. Neither my husband nor I could stomach this mush. Really sad about this food.
Had a great experience here with my kids. The food comes out fast and the service is just awesome. Prices are fair.

Was in the area with my wife and was looking for something to eat when we had stumbled across this amazing Thai spot we previously discussed how most Thai spots in our area had either shut down or had been operating at different times then usual so this was a delightful surprise and to be 100% honest this was what we were missing for starters the pineapple fried rice was everything and more I got the shrimp pineapple rice and she got the chicken pineapple rice both were great packed with flavor in every bite next was the ribs my wife loves ribs so it was to no surprise when she saw them she had to try and they did not disappoint flavorful ,decadent ,savory ribs they were a perfect addition to the rice next a appetizer I must mention the curry puff nothing like i ever had before cripsy croissant like texture with a sort of curry mash filling with a sweet cucumber vinegrete sauce this just sealed the deal and I didn't even mention the chicken dumpling with the spicey sauce great food great experience can't wait to try again
Amazing food, great prices and nice service! Would come back here for sure! The waitress was so nice!

Would have liked to continue ordering food from here, however quality has gone down considerably and when ordering drinks, Thai ice tea/coffee/iced tea lemonade, the cup is 95% ice and minimal beverage. With most businesses barely holding on throughout the pandemic the food quality & drink portions should be much better.  No longer ordering from them  ✌🏾

The food is good and tasty but the portions are small and they open up at 11:30am instead of 11:00am like most places.  There is only two ladies in front who are normally friendly but the rest of staff is rude. The wait for food is long. They really need to fix their customer service.

I decided to randomly try this place (since I work a few blocks away) a few days ago, and honestly, I should’ve tried it sooner. It could be because I was hungry or it could be the fact that it was my first time having ramen BUT the food was absolutely delicious. The taste, the smell, everything was just bomb.  BTW, I definitely plan on becoming a regular customer! I had the pork ramen but next time I think I might try the chicken.

Pretty bland. It's either super Americanized or just bad, I don't know which but they're the same thing anyway I guess. Either way if you like authentic Thai food, you should avoid this place. I had the Pad see ew, the tom yum gai, and thai fried rice. All three were less than mediocre. I want to be clear that I enjoy authentic food, I don't enjoy Americanized versions. So this review is written from that perspective.
Thai noodle soup taste so good even I had it when it wasn't hot and the staff are nice

Came here on a Saturday night around 630 pm. Able to find parking immediately on the street across from the restaurant. Not packed and was seated immediately. Ambience was casual with a nice vibe. Had actually ordered take out but opted to eat in instead at the last minute.
Food is tasty and to my liking. Not sweet as some other Thai restaurants do.
One of my favorite places to grab some food. excellent location, well kept, and awesome service. Very good job!

I love their noodles - boat noodle, duck noodle soup. Their standard Thai dishes like pad Thai and pad see ew, along with drunken noodle are all on point too. But the one dish that keeps me craving and coming back for more is the Crispy pork ka-prao, with an added fried egg. It's so good!
Had a very good experience in here with my son. The food comes fast and the service is just good. Prices are convenient.
A top place for Thai food. I love going here. Certainly worth a return visit.
People there is so rude, the woman who works there yell at a black man and made him leave the table

I typically go to this location to grab food because it's right down the block from my job. Everytime I go I typically have pleasant service except for the last few times. I don't know if it's due to the coronavirus but the last two times I went there the service was terrible. The first negative experience was with a lady at the front desk. I come in and I'm greeted with an attidude, as if I'm imposing on her time. Then she wants to debate about the price. I come here everyday and get it the same price everyday and she wants to charge me extra. The next day different lady, I get charged the price I typically receive. I open up my food and the rice is burnt. After I spent a good 20 minutes waiting for my food. The service is not what it used to be. Some people don't realize that customer service is the backbone of a good business. I won't be comming back.
I enjoy the food from this place a lot, really good and clean, highly recommend.

Although everything on their menu looks and smells delicious, I always get the Pad Thai with chicken and shrimp, sometimes with a side of peanut sauce. The flavor is great with or without the peanut sauce. They have hot tea available as well.
This place has great service and enjoyable menu. One of the best restaurant ever. The meals arrived quick and the rates were economical. Will definitely recommend this place.
Drunken noodles very good, I asked for spicy! Calamari not as crispy, but thai food is great
Awesome place, you must have the Pumpkin Thai Curry and Curry Puffs - you're welcome in advance

Piked the pad thai, although it felt a bit small. Also liked the panang curry, although the chicken could have been more integrated with the curry (check photo, chicken looks white). Looking forward trying their duck dishes! Order directly to the restaurant by phone or their website to get a 10% off and a stamp on their paper stampcard.
We ate here twice on our trip. Food was delish
(Translated by Google) Delicious  (Original) Delicioso
Delicious authentic Thai for delivery. Drunken noodles, pad see ew and Panang curry were amazing!

Recently ate here. There are a few vegan options so i ordered one and a side dish, and while it took a bit to prepare I was actually able to taste (despite the nasal congestion.) If you'd like to eat out but not gain weight, and lack self control, the portion sizes are not insane here.

From the first moment  you arrive in that restaurant  they give you a great feeling. Very warm team, it is a nice restaurant to go out with buddies or with your date. Great  cooking, talented  chef de cuisine, competitive  price and courteous  service. Warmly recommended.
It's delicious. Although the noodles are broken down, the sauce is really good. I think I'll visit often while I'm in New York. They're all kind.

Just like the name says, the food is yummy!  Favorite today was the Som Tam (green papaya salad), strong and spicy. Food and service really takes me back, I lived and worked in Thailand years ago, this is the real thing..
(Translated by Google) Delicious and cheap  (Original) Delicioso y barato
I ordered green curry that is so delicious and the flavor is so strong. All meal make me comfortable and very enjoy my dinner!!!

(Translated by Google) We went to dinner twice at the place. Great food and excellent service. Small but super cozy place.  (Original) Fomos jantar duas vezes no local. Comida ótima e atendimento excelente. Local pequeno mas super aconchegante.
Really reliable lunch spot for authentic Thai food. Curries are good too.
(Translated by Google) Nice food. Price ok. Here are the photos of what you ordered and a little of the menu.  (Original) Comida boa. Preço ok. Seguem as fotos do que pedidos e um pouco do menu.
I visit this spot a lot since I work nearby. I must say the service is always good and they keep the spot well organized at all times. Prices are convenient and they serve generous portions.
The food is great here. The space is limited and not very friendly to guests. Better to get food and go from here.
Quick service. Food is okay
Good place! Great food and quality service. Tasty food as well!
Man this place is absolutely amazing. Such an authentic experience. Every bite was simply delicious. Glad we stopped there randomly. Will def come back next time I'm in the area.
cool having lunch

We ate there on our second night in NYC on Nee Years Day. This was one of the few restaurants open on the holiday but we are so glad we choose this one! The food was absolutely spectacular! Brought me right back to my Asia travels! Perfect amounts of spice and great portion sizes. We got some dumplings, a soup, cashew nut chicken, and a red curry bowl. So good 😊
Quaint Thai restaurant. Good selection of food. Prompt service and warm hosts. Surprise little joint in FIDI for good and delicious Thai food.
Today at 3.29 pm.  I have a bad experience with a waitress. She's so aggressive and talking to me like shouting at me. Her eyes unfriendly to me a lot. Btw. Food is good. Service is low.
Nice little home in the wall spot

Very bad service. Ordered the lunch special online on Uber eats and it said it includes a soup. Upon delivery, there was no soup so I called the restaurant. They said if you order on UberEats, you do not get soup which does not make sense at all. The food was also not the best and there were barely any vegetables in my fried rice.
Very comfy and great food!
Cosy place. Tasty food. Reasonable price and good portions.
Good value lunch but not enough seating
Very nice place. Have been to quite a few places all over the city. This is one of the best ones I have been too. Service is good, casual ambiance and the quantity is also good.
I eat here a lot and thank God i still love it like the first time
The meals and service were ahead of our expectations. We surely liked the ambience of this restaurant. First-rate restaurant to take the family out for dinner.
Great quick place for lunch for work. Like the food.
Great for a normal dinner takeout. Pineapple fried rice is recommended
The place serves large dishes and for convenient pricing. friendly owner. Never disappointing.
Was pleasantly surprised - close to home made foods. My favorite Thai place in NY from now on.

Excellent Thai food, especially in the food desert FiDi. The lunch specials have plenty of food, and the owners are super nice. Line moves fast, and food is usually out before 10 minutes. Online ordering also gives  you a 10% discount on their website. The food is always hot for hours, and tastes delicious. I recommend the pad see ew with a little hot sauce.
I get to eat here a lot since I work close by. I love how the customer service is always good and they keep the place well kept all the time. Rates are convenient and they serve big portions.
Very warm inside, but food felt very fresh
Highly recommend it
Exzellent service, marvelous food, the best asian food in my life! I really do rencomand it!
This spot has first-rate service as well as tasty food. One of the best restaurant around here. The food and drinks came out quick and the rates are inexpensive. Recommended.
Beef noodle soup very tasty👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻 Highly recommend for Asian like us. 😊
This place never fails to deliver. They serve good food for affordable prices, there no long wait even when the place is full.
Lunch special chicken pad Thai was the worst I’ve ever had. It was a flavorless and soggy mess. Save your money and go elsewhere. Terrible. I’d give it 0 stars if I could.
This spot is worth visiting. They have large portions for affordable prices. Always well kept and with fantastic character. Would recommend to others.
I have been multiple times and i am always delighted by the service inside. The food is tasty and is authentic Thai food. The staff itself is Thai.
The food was too salty for me
The foods were amazing. This place was a hidden gems! Please try Tom Yum noodles soup.
Long line. I waited for my food for like 20 min and the order was wrong.
Being a vegetarian you have selected options left.. Among them at AROY DEE you will find the best mouth watering dishes you can have😋
A hidden gem! We got the veggie dumplings (delicious) with homeade soy sauce,and tofu massaman which had an amazing peanut sauce.  Friendly and helpful wait staff. Definitely coming back!

Fantastic food, fantastic service. This is one of the only places I know that REALLY crank up the spice level if you ask for it. Sure there's tears, boogers, regret, and a burning backside--but I always come back for more. Perfect for first dates, birthdays, anniversaries, baby showers, wakes, etc. I absolutely love this place so much.
Great service! Loved the Drunken Noodles and Thai Iced Tea.
This is my absolute favorite place to get chicken pad thai in the Financial District. I recommend it to anyone who is interested.
Delicious!

I used to go to another Thai place but they moved uptown so I gave this a try the other day. The food was pretty tasty and made fresh. I love noodles and they were perfect. Will def be back to try some of the lunch specials since I work in the area.
The atmosphere is cozy and both the Heaven Chicken, and the Sticky Rice were to die for

Small place, but bring a big appetite. I ordered the drunken noodles and my friend got the Pad Thai and we both enjoyed our orders. The standout was the curry puff which we split as an appetizer. Hard to do better in FiDi
Thai restaurant to take away or eat there, they are 4 small table. Authentic Thai!!!!
Too salty and wet for the fried rice
Good but small portions and overpriced

Portion is quite big but limited seating and the food was a bit too heavy. I got the drunken noodle and it was really salty. Thai iced tea was too sweet and the tom yum soup was too sour. Staff is very friendly and it's one of the few options nearby the office area.

Very disappointed. I got massaman curry & they put the rice in the same container as the vegetables & chicken so all the sauce gets absorbed. Also, they barely give you any vegetables or chicken - the whole thing is rice. And there are no peanuts which is a staple of massaman curry. Won’t be going back.
Best thai in FiDi
A very busy tiny Thai restaurant in downtown. Maybe I ordered the wrong dish. The $10 beef noodle soup was in such small portion that I couldn’t believe my eyes!
Really cute place with delicious fairly authentic food.
Perfect quick meal.

Omg, this place is awesome!!! If you like Thai food, this is the place for you. It's a little off the main streets, but totally worth looking for and finding. My favorite dish there was the curry puff appetizer, although all of the food was great. Good selection of cold tea drinks too. They also do to-go orders pretty often, so if you don't want to stay out and about, there's an option for you.
Don’t order delivery from this place. You will never get your food even after checking in

Small place, can get very crowded. Took some time to get my order, I will order in advance next time. Good food, friendly service, impressive menu for such a small place. Recommended if you are looking for a good Thai lunch in the financial district.

A neat little Thai spot in the heart of downtown. Quite cramped inside but the food is delicious. The decor is trendy as well.. there is indeed seating but be prepared to be brushed by my folks ordering their food. I got the beef Thai fried rice off the lunch special and it came out to less than $10. They’ve got 4 different hot oil sauces for your tasting pleasure. Will definitely be visiting this place again.
Pretty cool spot to chill
Food is awesome! Although,  service is a little bit slow. But worth the wait!
Small portion
username: Honestly Name a better place if you have one

caption: Good and fast food .. you can give it a try.. A small place though so may be better to order if during rush time.
Basic Thai food.. nothing special. A little over priced though. Service was pretty good.
Thai cuisine and fast service in a tiny location with few seating... i got the Tom Yum Noodle Soup...  nice and cheap meal for only $11 !!
The best Thai Tea lemonade I ever have.
Was good and delicious
$9.80 lunch special.  Took 15 mins for carryout and is the smallest portion of Thai I've ever received in NYC.  Tastes alight though.

A nice little Thai place with lunch special options. Although the portion seems smaller than it used to be, the service is quick! So not a bad choice for a quick thai lunch. My shrimp pad see ew cost around $10.
Okay but not great. The steamed veggie dumplings were quite good. The Pad Thai was overwhelmed by the to-sweet peanut sauce.
Great place for lunch. Get the Choo Chee Curry & Satay Chicken

I had my friend over for dinner and as you can imagine she obviously stopes eating her pad Thai as I found a green bug full of legs in my drunken noodles and they only refund my dish instead of the whole order. Never again.

Conveniently located, however.. it's probably one of the worst Thai food I've had. I ordered the drunken noodles online and requested it spicy. It was soggy and completely bland. There was a river of oil in my bowl. Would not be ordering from here again.

Aroy Dee is amazing! I can’t get enough of this place. I’ve had the tofu veggie green curry multiple times and just tried to fillet fish red curry for the first time. Never disappointed by the flavor or the quality of the food!
Delicious pad tai wonton soup and garlic chicken
Super crowded during the lunch hour. Food was alright but not worth the wait
Delicious quick food.  Diverse menu.

I ordered delivery and found a hair in my food. When I called to ask for my money back, they didn't believe me and asked that I hold onto the food because they were going to send someone to look at the hair and retrieve the uneaten food. I left the food untouched and no one ever came. I used to order from here a lot but it was such a bad experience I won't be doing that again.
Great for a quick bite after work. Fair prices,  tasty food and good servicr.

A gem in the rough if you like a proper Thai dish that isn't uncessarily fancy. Having been to Thailand and indulged in "ground pork with basil sauce and a fried egg", Aroy Dee will bring you back to Thailand with their version of the quinticesentail dish. It also clears your sinuses if you request the spicy version.
Cold food upon delivery, noodles completely dry. Spring rolls falling apart.
The delivery took nearly 2 hours, the food was cold when delivered and when I called to let them know I was given an attitude and put on hold. Nobody ever came back on the phone.
I love this place but they need to bring back the coconut juice
Small Thai restaurant. Ideal place for a quick meal. Staffs are friendly and price of the menu is reasonable.
My order was incorrect, but it wouldn't have mattered anyway because it was not tasty at all.
Waited 35 minutes at lunchtime for what can only be described as a small container of lackluster pad thai. Don't bother with this place.

Seemed like an authentic thai restaurant with thai crew and of course thai dishes.  I love thai food and have had it in many other countries, but this particular thai restaurant (and same with many NYC restaurants) serve salty food!  NYC people seem to use more salt in all their dishes.  the tom yum soup, the pad thai noodles, the fried rice were all too salty for my taste...and I am from Korea, where foods are already considered salty.
Good spot for lunch specials!
Nice enough Thai restaurant, quite small, note very pricey but not the best in the area it's head to compete when you are so close to China Town
Satisfies my Thai food craving every time!
Horrible!
Good shrimp drunken noodles, they give you only 5 shrimp :(
best thai place around
One of the better Thai restaurants in the financial district.  Prices are inline with the area.
(Translated by Google) Mukul Sharma  (Original) Mukul Sharma
I ordered the seafood soup. It was nicely seasoned. It had some unusual seafood  ingredients (not all were for my western palate). Small but relaxing space.
Service very good! Had thai basi fried rice very tasty! Good flavours! Was on a saturday

I tried this place for lunch the other day, ordering the Thai Fried Rice with chicken.  Unfortunately, the dish was lacking flavor and could have used salt.  My co-worker who ordered pad see ew had a similar complaint.  Otherwise, the restaurant itself is cozy, the staff is friendly and the lunch prices are reasonable.

Very good food, even smaller space. Expect a wait if you want to sit and eat. It's better to take it out and eat outside or in the office. If the weather is nice getting it to go and enjoying outside is great. The price is reasonable and the taste is pretty good. The staff work pretty quickly considering the small space.

Placed a delivery order for green curry and massaman curry. The food was delivered quickly. I give it 1 star because the curries were more oil than curry and tasted like salted oil. Just not ok. You have been warned.
Good lunch deals, tiny seating area. Crispy calamari is great, as is the pink tofu seafood soup
I love this shop! 22 Thai was closed it seemed but this place was open and I gotten some great Thai food! The lady was very sweet and took my order with no issues.
Very tasty food and raisonnable price. People working there very kind and helpfull
Good food at a good price...just expect to wait during the primetime lunch hours!

Aroy Dee in my view is the best Thai restaurant in Financial District. The space is tight but the lunch specials are quite good. I had a basil soft shelled crab and it was tasty. You can charge on credit card if you spend $10 and above.

Be careful when ordering the cashew chicken, the order taker got mine wrong and put in the Pad Soo Eew with chicken instead. When I pointed out her mistake she yelled at me. I got another scowl when I asked for chopsticks later.  Once I got my actual order it was mediocre. Too spicy (cashew chicken usually comes with a sweet sauce) and as others have mentioned the portions are quite small. Not worth it.
(Translated by Google) Very good face, the price of 9 knives is not expensive, recommended!  (Original) 很不错的面，9刀的价格也不算贵，推荐！

Tiny spot with great food. Had the pad Thai with chicken that came with a delicious chick pea carrot  soup for lunch special. My boyfriend had the chicken panang which was also delicious. It tastes good and is presented nicely too. Very satisfying.  Love little gems like this one.
Ignore the B rating, and do yourself a favor: get the pumpkin curry. I can't even...it was so good. Nigh intimate.
food is ok
Delicious and a great lunch special!

The Show was Great! Rachel Ferral knew how to make you laugh and get you into the Valentines Day mood with her Music. But the food was sub par. Our waitress started off by forgeting to take our order. My Girlfriend ordered their lobster ravioli which was clearly previously frozen, and the shrimp was WAY overcooked and rubbery. The Filet was brought to me well done, i ordered it medium. the mashed potatoes were hard, clumpy, and cold. The veggies tasted like frozen out of the bag then microwaved. I might go back to see a show and order a drink, but i would NEVER EVER order food there.
Living in Jackson Heights/Woodside, I chuckle when people say this place is good. But if you live or work in FiDi and are dying for somewhat Americanized Thai food, it'll do.
Really good spicy noodle dishes. Roadside noodles were absolutely delicious! Pad se eiw was the best we have ever had. What a great hole in the wall!
One of the best locations for ramen in fidi
Prices are too high, portions too small. The food tastes great though.
Amazing Thai chicken fried rice
If the space wasn't small... I would give 5 stars. Food is super yummy!
Good fast and affordable. Food tastes good and service is fast. Good neighborhood standby.

LOVE THIS PLACE. super fast take out. Good cheap food. All their noodle dishes are really good and since I love spicy, they always accommodate to my liking and send extra hot sauces on the side. I always order an extra side of sticky rice to munch on later or the next day.... guilty pleasure.
Good lunch. Freshly made
Absolutely delicious. Authentic Thai food, just like when I lived there! :)

Decent lunch spot if you work in the area, but you'll probably need to supplement it with appetizers and/or dessert. Lunch specials are inexpensive, but portions are small. The taste is authentic enough for me, and the pad thai, which is usually oversauced at restaurants, was al dente with the right amount of flavoring.
Best Thai in the fidi.

This is a fast food Thai restaurant. The food is really good. It is prepared very quickly. The staff is very nice and helpful. If you are dining during lunch, then order one of the lunch specials. I had the chicken heaven with ginger rice and sweet chili sauce. The spicy sauce mixed with the ginger was a burst of flavor in my mouth. Delicious. The drunken noodles with chicken or shrimp is really good. The appetizers are good. I had the Thai bar b que ribs, shrimp and chicken dumplings, and the curry puff. All were good. They offer an extensive menu. The restaurant is small. The prices are very reasonable.

Small space but great lunch deals and good food! One of the few place I've tried more than 2-3 meals on their menu and liked! My favorite is thing to order is Pad See Ew w/ beef it's thicker noodles and very filling. My only complaint is that lunch hour is getting busier and busier there so I have to order my food in advanced.
Unfortunately the food was terrible and when I said something to the waitress she  was very unfriendly. We left the plates nearly uneaten.

Aroy Dee is a great addition to the neighborhood. It's also the best Thai restaurant in the Financial District so far. Ordered via Seamless - food was delivered steaming hot and on time. I am a fan of their pineapple fried rice - it came with good amount of veggies (pineapple, tomato, etc.) and your choice of meat.  Price is also reasonable. I'd definitely try other dishes at this restaurant.
Just great. Fast, friendly, and most importantly, delicious. If you live nearby and don't eat here once a week, you're doing it wrong.
